        "title": "fix(commands): keep slash handling off reply startup",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis extracts the slash-command startup portion of #85941 into a focused PR.\n\n- keep slash-command handler loading out of reply startup work\n- tighten command info/session-store behavior around startup-time command metadata\n- add focused command-info coverage for the lazy path\n- keep the original contributor commit author: Keshav's Bot <keshavbotagent@gmail.com>\n\nSplit from #85941 so the command-runtime surface can be reviewed independently. Thanks @keshavbotagent for the original work.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check origin/main...origin/codex/split-85941-command-startup`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: reply startup no longer has to eagerly pull slash-command handling work just to expose command metadata.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout on fresh `origin/main` split branch.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `git diff --check origin/main...origin/codex/split-85941-command-startup`.\nEvidence after fix: split branch cherry-picked cleanly onto current `origin/main`; whitespace/conflict sanity passed.\nObserved result after fix: no diff-check errors; commit author preserved as Keshav's Bot <keshavbotagent@gmail.com>.\nWhat was not tested: focused command Vitest was not rerun after the split; CI should run the normal PR gates.\n",
